snippet.title: Mom Hijacked outside Kloof pre primary school

localized.description:
READ ME
**************
Caught on a ENFORCE Security Camera, Give a LIKE for ENFORCE Security !!!
At 07:00 on 8 July 2014 , an unsuspecting mother was hijacked of her vehicle, outside a school in the Kloof area, KZN.

 The entire ordeal was caught on one of our Enforce Watchmen Camera's and the footage has been handed over to the SAPS to aid them in their investigation.

 At the start of the video the mother arrives, parks and sees to her child. The three suspects make their first appearance in the video at the 50 second mark.

 The suspects casually walk across the parking lot and hang around the recycling bin until the unsuspecting mother returns.

 At the 1:30 mark, the suspects notice the mother returning and move in towards her. They hold her up by gunpoint, just outside the view of the camera and demand the keys.

 Two members of the public, who notice the scene unfolding, make a brave attempt to block the suspects in. The suspects who remained calm and casual throughout the hijacking, point the firearm at the drivers attempting to assist, forcing them to retreat for safety reasons.

 The mother was thankfully not injured in anyway and the vehicle has unfortunately not yet been recovered.

Thank you to enforce who captured this.
Comments and opinions are welcome.
Mom Hijacked outside Kloof pre primary school
Mom hijacked outside school
